---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { breadcrumbSchema } from '../data/seo';

const title = 'Terms and Conditions | The Reflex Hub';
const description =
  'Read the terms and conditions for using The Reflex Hub. Plain language rules for our free reaction, typing, memory, and aim tests. Updated July 2026.';
const path = '/terms-and-conditions';

const schema = [
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', path: '/' },
    { name: 'Terms and Conditions', path },
  ]),
];
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} path={path} schema={schema}>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 pt-8">
    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold">Terms and Conditions</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-muted">Effective date: July 12, 2026</p>

    <article class="copy mt-6">
      <p>
        Welcome to The Reflex Hub. These terms and conditions govern your use of thereflexhub.com and all games, tests,
        and content available on it (the "Site"). By accessing or using the Site, you agree to these terms. If you do
        not agree with any part of them, please do not use the Site. We have kept the language as plain as possible,
        because terms you cannot understand protect nobody.
      </p>

      <h2>1. What the Site Is</h2>
      <p>
        The Reflex Hub provides free browser games that measure skills such as reaction time, clicking speed, typing
        speed, memory, and aim. The Site is provided for entertainment, practice, and casual self measurement. It is
        not a medical, psychological, or professional assessment service, and no score or result on the Site should be
        used to evaluate a health condition, fitness to drive, or fitness for any occupation.
      </p>

      <h2>2. Acceptable Use</h2>
      <p>You agree to use the Site only for lawful purposes. In particular, you agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use bots, scripts, auto-clickers, or other automation to interact with the games or misrepresent scores.</li>
        <li>Attempt to disrupt, overload, or interfere with the operation or security of the Site.</li>
        <li>Copy, scrape, republish, or redistribute substantial portions of the Site's content without permission.</li>
        <li>Use the Site in any way that violates applicable laws or regulations in your jurisdiction.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Intellectual Property</h2>
      <p>
        The Site's design, text, graphics, game code, and branding are the property of The Reflex Hub and are protected
        by copyright and other intellectual property laws. You may link to any page on the Site and share your results
        freely. You may not copy the Site's content or games for republication, resale, or the creation of a competing
        service without prior written consent. Third party names mentioned on the Site, such as game titles and
        trademarks, belong to their respective owners and are referenced for identification only.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Scores and Local Data</h2>
      <p>
        Your scores, personal bests, run history, and preferences are stored locally in your own browser using
        localStorage. They are not uploaded to our servers and we cannot restore them if they are lost. Clearing your
        browser data, switching browsers or devices, or using private browsing will remove or bypass this data. Scores
        have no monetary value, confer no rights, and may be affected by your hardware and browser, as explained in our
        content about measurement accuracy.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Advertising and Third Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        The Site may display advertising and may use privacy focused analytics to understand aggregate traffic. Ads are
        provided by third parties who may use cookies or similar technologies as described in our
        <a href="/privacy-policy">privacy policy</a>. We do not control and are not responsible for the content of
        external websites linked from the Site, including advertiser sites. Visiting external links is at your own
        discretion.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis, without warranties of any kind, whether express or
        implied, including but not limited to implied warranties of merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose,
        accuracy, and non-infringement. We do not warrant that the Site will be uninterrupted, error free, or free of
        harmful components, or that scores and measurements will be precise on every combination of hardware, browser,
        and network.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, The Reflex Hub and its operators shall not be liable for any indirect,
        incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or for any loss of data, profits, or goodwill, arising
        out of or related to your use of the Site. This includes, without limitation, damages arising from reliance on
        any score or measurement, loss of locally stored data, or temporary unavailability of the Site. Where liability
        cannot be excluded, it is limited to the amount you paid to use the Site, which is zero, or the smallest amount
        permitted by applicable law.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Health and Safety</h2>
      <p>
        Some games involve rapid repeated clicking, tapping, or typing. Take regular breaks, stop immediately if you
        feel pain or discomfort in your hands, wrists, or arms, and consult a professional if discomfort persists. If
        you are sensitive to flashing or rapidly changing colors, use your judgment before playing games with fast
        color changes. You use the games at your own risk.
      </p>

      <h2>9. Children</h2>
      <p>
        The Site is a general audience website and is not directed at children under 13. We do not knowingly collect
        personal information from anyone, including children; see the <a href="/privacy-policy">privacy policy</a> for
        details on our minimal data practices.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to the Site and These Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may add, change, or remove games and features at any time without notice. We may also update these terms
        from time to time. The effective date at the top of this page shows when they were last revised, and continued
        use of the Site after a revision constitutes acceptance of the updated terms. If a change is significant, we
        will make that clear on this page.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Severability</h2>
      <p>
        If any provision of these terms is found to be unenforceable, the remaining provisions will continue in full
        force and effect, and the unenforceable provision will be replaced by an enforceable one that most closely
        matches its intent.
      </p>

      <h2>12. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about these terms are welcome. Reach us through the <a href="/contact">contact page</a> and we will
        respond as soon as we can.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
